ritics and publicists, Gert Ueding, was honoured with a festschrift by the School of Rhetoric at the University of Tübingen. In their contributions, his friends, companions and colleagues reflect the wide range of Gerd Ueding’s interests, which encompass classical philosophy and rhetoric as much as popular authors such as Karl May and Wilhelm Busch, philosophers such as Aristotle, Bloch and Hegel, together with contemporary modern literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aLiteraturexHistory and criticism. 0aRhetoricxHistory. 0aRhetoric. 4aHermeneutik. 4aLiteraturkritik. 4aRhetorik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aHermeneutics, Literary Criticism, Rhetoric.1 aBeetz, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDyck, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGahse, Zsuzsanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHagemann, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHinck, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHochhuth, Rolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolländer, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHölderlin, Friedrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalivoda, Gregor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnape, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnape, Joachim, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKopperschmidt, Josef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKorff, Friedrich Wilhelm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 